Shift4/Lighthouse Timeline
For discussion purposes only. Prepared at the request of counsel.

Date	Event/Transaction
Pre-2015	Shift4 and First Data entered into an agreement (the "2006 Agreement") pursuant to which Shift4 was paid residuals for referring merchants to First
Data.

06/03/15	First Data and Lighthouse entered into the Reseller Agreement (the "2015 Agreement"). Shift4 was not a party to this agreement.

06/24/15	Lighthouse (f/k/a Harbortouch) was "spun out" by Shift4 and became a separate legal entity with J.R.R. serving as the sloe member.

07/16/18	First Data gives notice of its intent to terminate the 2006 Agreement with Shift4.

07/20/18	Shift4 gives notice of its intent to offset by $5.5 million the "true-up" payment owed to First Data due to the temination of the 2006 Agreement.

08/15/18	The 2006 Agreement terminated.

08/31/18	First Data pays Shift4 the first true-up payment ($1.6 million), despite Shift4;s stated intent to offset the full $5.5 million that was owed.

12/02/18	Shift4 withheld $5.5 million from FDP (the "Offset").

01/16/19	Fiserv's acquisition of First Data is announced.

01/31/19	First Data pays Shift4 its final qtrly true-up payment, approx. $1.1 million.

Spring 2019	[REDACTED]

05/19	[REDACTED]

[REDACTED] JRR's last conversion with [REDACTED] President of Card Connect, about the dispute.

04/29/19	[REDACTED] requests financial information from Shift4/Lighthouse to support its claimed 2018 losses, but Shift4 failed to provide it.

06/18/19	The dispute relating to the 2006 Agreement settles.

07/01/19	[REDACTED] and [REDACTED] speak for the first time.

07/29/19	Fiserv's Acquition of First Data closes.

08/20/19	This lawsuits is filed.

11/07/19	JRR threatens to use media outlet to smear Fiserv/Card Connect.

11/22/19	Parties participate in a mediation before Judge [REDACTED] (Ret.).

06/12/2020    JRR sends demand letter to Fiserv.
